result.name: What The Pho

reviews.text: Great selection of Thai and Vietnamese cuisine.  Curry beef brisket with rice is always my favorite dish.  Good Asian atmosphere with Vietnamese songs always playing in the background.  Also a great variety of beverages, must go if you love Thai and Vietnamese food.

I just had the worst coffee ever! They just made it with instant coffee powder and delivered to my table 1 min after I ordered. It tasted so cheap and artificial. The curry chicken was average, yet this lunch set coated $72. Definitely overpriced for such quality in this residential area.

High price and poor quality. Very small portion. The shrimp cake in the photo costs $68. 
The pho are overcooked. I can't even finish my drink coz it's too lousy. Service is also below average.

The menu here is enormous so I can't comment on the food overall, but what we did have was great. Lovely mango salad, Beef Pho and Pork Neck wraps. Service was good and the atmosphere is pleasant too. Only thing that I found mildly irritating was that the 'appetizers' we ordered came at the very end, why label them appetizers, boooo. Otherwise loved it.
Way below standard food yet not cheap
